cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper discusses the architecture and mathematical theory behind Convolution Neural Networks (CNN), which are widely used in visual imagery applications such as object classification and speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning frameworks such as Tensorflow and Keras, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses activation functions and loss functions, which are important topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions speech recognition, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
